# /etc/default/astro-process on the eclipticam Pi.
#
# The eclipticam Pi does NOT run stage 3 (deliverables). Stage 3 runs on
# puppy, where the frames physically live — a Pi running its own stage 3
# would read every frame back over NFS on a weak CPU (~13x slower than
# puppy reading locally; proven by the astrocam backfill, 2026-06-20).
# The Pis do stage 1 (astro-state) + capture only. astro-process.service
# is intentionally DISABLED on this Pi; puppy's astro-process processes
# eclipticam-v1/-v3w (see services/astro-process.env.puppy).
#
# A Pi can only do the pipeline calculation ("self") once it gains its
# own LOCAL storage for its frames — then "self" means processing local
# data, not pulling it back over NFS. Until then keep CAMERAS empty here
# so an accidentally-enabled service is a no-op, not a slow duplicate of
# puppy's work.
CAMERAS=""
